        <num>CCP 2006</num>
        <heading>2006.  Court where action brought</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2006.  Court where action brought
An action to annul a judgment must be brought in the trial court, even though the judgment sought to be annulled may have been affirmed on appeal, or even rendered by the appellate court.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
